Vitellaria were not observed. The oval-shaped ovaries ( Fig. 13A : ov) are located rostrally from the copulatory bulb. The oocytes are organised in a row. The oviducts ( Fig. 13A : od) open into the proximal end of the female duct. The female duct ( Fig. 12D, 12F & 13A : fd) opens into the receptacle bursa (terminology of Karling 1981; followed by
Reygel et al. 2011
) ( Fig. 13A : rb) through a sphincter ( Fig. 13A : sph). The caudally-located bursa ( Fig. 12D, 12F & 13A : b) opens into the female genital atrium via the bursal stalk. The uterus ( Fig. 13A : ut) has a sphincter more or less at its midpoint. The common gonopore ( Fig. 13A : cg) opens at 90%.
